stanford hosp logo lpch logo page 1 stanford university medical center family abuse prevention council fapc fapc is an officially recognized council charged with improving the well being of our patients and medical center personnel by addressing the issue of family abuse in all of its forms our group includes nursing social work employees physicians and administrators from stanford hospital and clinics lucile packard children's hospital and the stanford school of medicine our goals are to standardize and monitor legally required abuse screening of our patients improve student personnel education and training in recognizing and responding to patients who have been abused provide safety and referral information for patients provide resources for employees and managers in supporting co workers with home abuse difficulties stimulate medical related research on the problem of abuse outreach to the medical and general community to join our council or if you have questions or comments contact domesticabuse med stanford edu http domesticabuse stanford edu http elderabuse stanford edu http childabuse stanford edu
